Modifying Docker Images
Method 1: Modify a Running Container
1.	Run container without --rm
2.	Make required changes
3.	Exit container
4.	List containers:
sudo docker ps -a
5.	Commit changes:
sudo docker commit <container_id> newrepo:newtag
________________________________________
Method 2: Modify Using Dockerfile (Recommended)
1.	Use existing image in FROM
2.	Add software/data using RUN, COPY, pip install, wget
3.	Build a new image 
sudo docker build -t newim:v3 .
âœ”ï¸ Reproducible and maintainable
